This check is important. Optional might be empty
Good point.  FIxed.
this also fixes copies, right?
I don't think so.  It wasn't a copy before, it just changes a pointer to a reference.
oh, missed the "*". Ack
add const here as well? I believe if get_ptr is template with const in the first place, `uint64_t* preValue = get_ptr` will error out.

I don't see a const overload for get_ptr, but I can try:

https://json.nlohmann.me/api/basic_json/get_ptr/#template-parameters
Looks like it worked. Done.
For the future, before we merge, I think a "Tested: Code builds." is better than "Tested: WIP"
agreed.  I usually try to do that but I missed it up this time

not related to this commit, but this brace init can be omitted, right? We just can do 

```
[resName, service, asyncResp]
```

Yep.  I suspect what they meant to do was asyncResp{std::move(asyncResp)} which in theory saves a shared_ptr copy, but because shared_ptr copies are inexpensive to make, we generally just allow the copy.
